The paper focuses on the use of machine learning algorithms for detecting malware in PDF files, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial machine learning techniques to evade detection, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques for analyzing PDF files, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses potential defense mechanisms for mitigating the impact of attacks on malware detectors, which is a topic of interest in software engineering (cs.SE).
